title: Cobden volleyball team in action
text: The Cobden High School volleyball team had a busy schedule during September. The Lady Appleknockers participated in the Carrier Mills Tournament on Sept. 12. Gallatin County beat Cobden in three sets, 25-21, 18-25 and 15-14 (first to 15 won.) Sara Millis had six kills, Carley Washer had six kills and Taylor Tomazzoli had five kills. Cobden then beat Carrier Mills in two sets, 25-21 and 25-22. Taylor Tomazzoli had 12 kills, Carley Washer had five kills and Aubrey Glasco had 26 assists. Cobden beat Galatia in two sets, 25-19 and 25-15. Carley Washer had six kills, Taylor Tomazzoli had seven kills and Aubrey Glasco had 24 assists. Cobden beat NCEO in the championship match in three sets, 25-16, 22-25 and 15-8. Aubrey Glasco had 38 assists, Sara Millis had 10 kills and Taylor Tomazzoli had 14 kills. The Lady Appleknockers faced host Joppa on Sept. 15. Cobden beat Joppa in two sets, 25-11 and 25-9. Meredith Flamm had three aces, Sara Millis had six kills and Taylor Tomazzoli had seven kills. Cobden beat host Meridian on Sept. 17 in two sets, 25-17 and 25-10. Carley Washer had six kills, Sara Millis had four kills and Taylor Tomazzoli had seven kills. The Lady Appleknockers participated in the Massac Tournament on Sept. 19. Massac beat Cobden in two sets, 25-21 and 25-16. Sara Millis had three kills, Taylor Tomazzoli had eight kills and Aubrey Glasco had 13 assists. Centralia beat Cobden in two sets, 25-14 and 25-21. Sara Millis had six kills and Aubrey Glasco had 13 assists. Cobden beat Eldorado in two sets, 25-21 and 25-14. Sara Millis had five kills, Taylor Tomazzoli had six kills and Aubrey Glasco had 18 assists. The Lady Appleknockers participated in the Trico Tournament on Sept. 22-24. On Tuesday, Sept. 22, Cobden beat Steeleville in two sets, 21-16 and 22-20. Sara Millis had 10 kills, Taylor Tomazzoli had 11 kills and Aubrey Glasco had 21 assists. On Tuesday, Sept. 22, Cobden beat Chester in two sets, 21-18 and 21-18. Aubrey Glasco had 14 assists, Sara Millis had five kills and Carley Washer had four kills. On Wednesday, Sept. 23, Cobden beat Sparta in two sets, 21-14 and 21-11. Sara Millis had five kills, Aubrey Glasco had eight assists and Meredith Flamm had six aces. On Wednesday, Sept. 23, Trico beat Cobden in two sets, 21-8 and 21-9. Taylor Tomazzoli had three kills, Sara Millis had two kills and Aubrey Glasco had six assists. On Thursday, Sept. 24, Cobden beat Marissa in two sets, 21-17 and 21-15. Sara Millis had eight kills, Meredith Flamm had four kills and Aubrey Glasco had 16 assists. The Lady Appleknockers finished 2nd in the Trico Tournament.
